        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3409236131?book_show_action=true">Jun 24, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brady" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brady" href="/user/show/37323125-brady">Brady</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780887480218" href="/book/show/150320.Thomas_and_Beulah">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/37323125-brady?shelf=grad-school">grad-school</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/37323125-brady?shelf=african-american-lit">african-american-lit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/37323125-brady?shelf=poetry">poetry</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3409236131" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14867315102458034903">Overall, I liked this poetry collection, but didn&apos;t love it. To be fair, I&apos;m not a big poetry fan to begin with. Poetry is usually the last thing I reach for when reading for pleasure.<br/><br/>As for the poems, some of them were vivid and wonderful, highlighting tender and nostalgic moments from Thomas and Beulah&apos;s past. Others, were...well...very cryptic and abstract. All in all, not something I would ever pick up by choice, but a decent read regardless.</span>
  <span id="freeText14867315102458034903" style="display:none">Overall, I liked this poetry collection, but didn't love it. To be fair, I'm not a big poetry fan to begin with. Poetry is usually the last thing I reach for when reading for pleasure.<br /><br />As for the poems, some of them were vivid and wonderful, highlighting tender and nostalgic moments from Thomas and Beulah's past. Others, were...well...very cryptic and abstract. All in all, not something I would ever pick up by choice, but a decent read regardless.</span>
